1253
01:23:36,611 --> 01:23:38,579
- ln any league.
- Got that right.

1254
01:23:38,646 --> 01:23:42,446
Did you hear what l said?
l'm going to the Show.

1255
01:23:43,551 --> 01:23:47,043
You know what the difference
between hitting 250 and 300 is?

1256
01:23:47,789 --> 01:23:50,349
lt's 25 hits.

1257
01:23:50,425 --> 01:23:54,794
Twenty-five hits
in 500 at-bats is 500 points.

1258
01:23:54,863 --> 01:23:58,026
There's six months in a season.
That's about 25 weeks.

1259
01:23:58,099 --> 01:24:01,296
That means if you get
one extra flare a week.

1260
01:24:01,369 --> 01:24:03,803
A gork. You get a ground ball.

1261
01:24:03,872 --> 01:24:06,170
You get a ground ball
with eyes.

1262
01:24:06,241 --> 01:24:08,505
You get a dying quail.

1263
01:24:09,978 --> 01:24:12,708
Just one more dying quail a week...

1264
01:24:12,781 --> 01:24:14,476
and you're in Yankee Stadium.

1265
01:24:16,317 --> 01:24:18,683
You still don't know
what l'm talking about.

1266
01:24:18,753 --> 01:24:20,687
Get the hell outta here.

1267
01:24:20,755 --> 01:24:22,985
All right.

1268
01:24:23,058 --> 01:24:24,685
Fuck.

1269
01:24:24,759 --> 01:24:26,727
Send you a postcard.

1270
01:24:26,795 --> 01:24:28,660
Send me a postcard?
Hey, l made it.

1271
01:24:28,730 --> 01:24:30,425
You made it.
You made shit.

1272
01:24:30,498 --> 01:24:32,489
Hey!

1273
01:24:35,737 --> 01:24:37,034
You crazy?

1274
01:24:37,105 --> 01:24:38,732
What the hell's
wrong with you?

1275
01:24:38,807 --> 01:24:41,776
- l'll be all right.
- l'm talking about my mirror.

1276
01:24:43,244 --> 01:24:45,678
Shit, l'm sorry. Hey!

1277
01:24:45,747 --> 01:24:47,408
l'm not gonna fight you.

1278
01:24:47,482 --> 01:24:49,677
What do you mean you're not gonna
fight me, you fuck?

1279
01:24:49,751 --> 01:24:52,015
Why am l a fuck?

1280
01:24:52,087 --> 01:24:53,349
Because you got talent.

1281
01:24:53,421 --> 01:24:56,185
l got brains,
but you got talent.

1282
01:24:57,625 --> 01:25:01,061
See this right arm?
Worth a million bucks a year.

1283
01:25:01,129 --> 01:25:03,825
All my limbs put together
aren't worth seven cents a pound.

1284
01:25:03,898 --> 01:25:05,798
What are you talking about?
You're a great catcher.

1285
01:25:05,867 --> 01:25:08,802
l'm a great catcher?

1286
01:25:08,870 --> 01:25:10,963
- Forget it.
- Hey.

1287
01:25:11,039 --> 01:25:12,529
- Fucking forget it.
- Hey, Meat.

1288
01:25:15,643 --> 01:25:17,406
Damn!

1289
01:25:18,480 --> 01:25:20,311
l didn't mean to hit you.

1290
01:25:23,585 --> 01:25:25,780
You hurt my eye!

1291
01:25:26,955 --> 01:25:28,582
Sorry.

1292
01:25:28,656 --> 01:25:32,558
Did you hit me with
your right or left?

1293
01:25:34,362 --> 01:25:37,195
Did you hit me with your right hand
or with your left?

1294
01:25:37,265 --> 01:25:38,254
My left.

1295
01:25:38,333 --> 01:25:40,198
That's good.

1296
01:25:40,268 --> 01:25:43,567
You get in a fight with a drunk,
you don't hit with your pitching hand.

1297
01:25:44,539 --> 01:25:47,770
l can't keep giving you
these free lessons.

1298
01:25:47,842 --> 01:25:50,470
Quit screwing around
and help me up.

1299
01:25:57,185 --> 01:25:58,675
You look great, man.

1300
01:26:10,165 --> 01:26:12,599
Be careful with those now.

1301
01:26:12,667 --> 01:26:14,601
We got a boy going to the Show.

1302
01:26:44,299 --> 01:26:46,233
Sorry about last night.

1303
01:26:50,538 --> 01:26:51,903
Forget it.

1304
01:26:54,842 --> 01:26:58,073
l have been known
on occasion to...

1305
01:26:58,146 --> 01:26:59,909
howl at the moon.

1306
01:27:01,382 --> 01:27:02,940
You understand?

1307
01:27:08,022 --> 01:27:09,546
No.

1308
01:27:09,624 --> 01:27:11,717
Well, you will.

1309
01:27:14,062 --> 01:27:15,927
Look, Nuke...

1310
01:27:15,997 --> 01:27:19,057
these big-league hitters are going to
light you up like a pinball machine...

1311
01:27:19,133 --> 01:27:21,761
for a while, all right?

1312
01:27:21,836 --> 01:27:23,599
Don't worry about it.

1313
01:27:23,671 --> 01:27:27,505
You be cocky and arrogant,
even when you're getting beat.

1314
01:27:29,210 --> 01:27:30,700
That's the secret.

1315
01:27:32,914 --> 01:27:36,941
You gotta play this game
with fear and arrogance.

1316
01:27:38,920 --> 01:27:40,478
Fear and ignorance.

1317
01:27:41,956 --> 01:27:46,689
No, fear and arrogance,
you hayseed, not ignorance.

1318
01:27:46,761 --> 01:27:49,229
l know.

1319
01:27:49,297 --> 01:27:51,697
l just like seeing you
get all worked up.

1320
01:27:58,139 --> 01:27:59,231
Listen.

1321
01:28:03,111 --> 01:28:04,305
Thanks.

1322
01:28:21,562 --> 01:28:22,756
Hey, Nuke.

1323
01:28:24,966 --> 01:28:26,957
Good luck.

1324
01:28:27,035 --> 01:28:29,595
You too...

1325
01:28:29,671 --> 01:28:30,933
Meat.

1326
01:28:50,491 --> 01:28:53,016
l now pronounce you
husband and wife.

1327
01:28:53,094 --> 01:28:54,686
You may kiss the bride.

1328
01:29:27,762 --> 01:29:32,324
Jimmy, we all pitched in,
and we got you a little gift.

1329
01:29:32,400 --> 01:29:33,389
Tony.

1330
01:29:33,468 --> 01:29:36,369
Kind of a special wedding cake
from the Durham Bulls.

1331
01:29:39,307 --> 01:29:41,400
Oh, my Lord!

1332
01:29:46,814 --> 01:29:49,681
Yeah, Skip?

1333
01:29:49,751 --> 01:29:51,685
You wanted to see me?

1334
01:29:52,420 --> 01:29:55,878
Crash, shut the door.

1335
01:30:00,995 --> 01:30:02,087
l wanna thank everyone!

1336
01:30:02,163 --> 01:30:03,926
Gimme a piece of that!

1337
01:30:16,344 --> 01:30:19,279
This is the toughest job
a manager has.

1338
01:30:22,617 --> 01:30:23,709
But...

1339
01:30:26,854 --> 01:30:29,345
the organization
wants to make a change.

1340
01:30:30,658 --> 01:30:35,425
Now that Nuke's gone, they wanna
bring up some young catcher.

1341
01:30:35,496 --> 01:30:38,090
Some kid hitting 300
in Bluefield.

1342
01:30:38,166 --> 01:30:40,566
He's probably a bust.

1343
01:30:40,635 --> 01:30:43,866
l put in a word for you
with the organization.

1344
01:30:43,938 --> 01:30:48,272
Told them l thought you might make
a fine minor-league manager someday.

1345
01:30:50,878 --> 01:30:55,372
There might be an opening
at Visalia next year.

1346
01:30:58,386 --> 01:31:00,445
You had a hell
of a year, Crash.

1347
01:31:01,989 --> 01:31:03,217
But...

1348
01:31:04,392 --> 01:31:06,326
you know how it is.

1349
01:32:29,644 --> 01:32:31,578
l got released.

1350
01:32:32,813 --> 01:32:34,337
l heard already.

1351
01:33:50,758 --> 01:33:52,726
Oh, my.

1352
01:34:50,885 --> 01:34:53,353
l think probably with my love
for four-legged creatures...

1353
01:34:53,421 --> 01:34:56,288
and hooves and everything,
that in another lifetime...

1354
01:34:56,357 --> 01:34:59,121
l was probably Catherine the Great
or Francis of Assisi.

1355
01:34:59,193 --> 01:35:01,127
l'm not sure which one.

1356
01:35:02,430 --> 01:35:04,057
What do you think, honey?

1357
01:35:06,267 --> 01:35:08,633
How come in former lifetimes...

1358
01:35:08,703 --> 01:35:10,694
everybody is somebody famous?

1359
01:35:20,414 --> 01:35:23,440
How come nobody ever says
they were "Joe Schmoe"?

1360
01:35:23,517 --> 01:35:26,816
Because it doesn't work
that way, you fool.

1361
01:35:35,296 --> 01:35:36,991
God, you are gorgeous.

1362
01:35:39,867 --> 01:35:41,562
You wanna dance?

1363
01:35:56,917 --> 01:35:58,009
Yes.

1364
01:35:58,886 --> 01:36:00,820
l guess you do.

1365
01:38:34,408 --> 01:38:37,309
Crash took off at dawn.

1366
01:38:37,378 --> 01:38:39,471
Said he heard there might be
an opening for a catcher...

1367
01:38:39,546 --> 01:38:41,537
in Asheville
on the South Atlantic League.

1368
01:38:42,750 --> 01:38:47,517
A woman should be so strong
that she's not affected by such things.

1369
01:38:47,588 --> 01:38:50,113
lt wasn't the first time
l went to bed with a guy...

1370
01:38:50,190 --> 01:38:52,556
and woke up with a note.

1371
01:38:52,626 --> 01:38:55,322
At least the son of a bitch
left me breakfast.

1372
01:38:57,965 --> 01:39:02,061
You have to respect a ballplayer
who's trying to finish the season.

1373
01:39:02,136 --> 01:39:04,400
At least,
that's what l told myself.

1374
01:39:05,439 --> 01:39:08,704
Baseball may be a religion
full of magic cosmic truth...

1375
01:39:08,776 --> 01:39:11,870
in the fundamental ontological
riddles of our time...

1376
01:39:11,946 --> 01:39:13,971
but it's also a job.

1377
01:39:15,816 --> 01:39:18,808
Come on, Meat.
Throw me that weak-ass shit.

1378
01:39:20,321 --> 01:39:22,551
You ain't gettin'
that cheese by me.

1379
01:39:22,623 --> 01:39:24,955
Bring it.

1380
01:39:27,661 --> 01:39:32,598
When Crash hit his 2 4 7th home run,
l knew the moment it happened.

1381
01:39:32,666 --> 01:39:34,395
But l'm sure nobody else did.

1382
01:39:34,468 --> 01:39:37,904
And The Sporting News
didn't say anything about it.

1383
01:39:39,707 --> 01:39:42,938
"Full many a flower is born
to blush unseen.

1384
01:39:43,010 --> 01:39:45,672
And waste its sweetness
on the desert air. "

1385
01:39:45,746 --> 01:39:47,873
Thomas Gray.

1386
01:39:47,948 --> 01:39:49,540
Or William Cullen Bryant.

1387
01:39:49,616 --> 01:39:51,584
l don't know.
l get 'em mixed up.

1388
01:39:51,652 --> 01:39:55,520
Anyway, my attempts at housekeeping
were feeble as usual.

1389
01:39:55,589 --> 01:39:58,558
l sometimes
get easily distracted.

1390
01:39:58,625 --> 01:40:01,958
Funny thing was
l stopped worrying about Nuke.

1391
01:40:02,029 --> 01:40:04,759
Somehow l knew
nothing would stop him.

1392
01:40:04,832 --> 01:40:08,928
The world is made for people
who aren't cursed with self-awareness.

1393
01:40:09,003 --> 01:40:12,097
Crash was right--
Nuke had a gift.

1394
01:40:12,172 --> 01:40:16,131
l'm just happy to be here,
and l hope l can help the ball club.

1395
01:40:16,210 --> 01:40:18,144
You know, l just wanna
give it my best shot...

1396
01:40:18,212 --> 01:40:20,442
and good Lord willing,
things will work out.

1397
01:40:20,514 --> 01:40:22,744
You gotta play them
one day at a time, though.

1398
01:40:22,816 --> 01:40:24,750
Raye Anne, right?
That's a beautiful name.

1399
01:40:24,818 --> 01:40:28,185
ls that Greek?
lt's a beautiful name.

1400
01:40:28,255 --> 01:40:30,723
There's a great song by Motley Crue.
Do you know it?

1401
01:40:30,791 --> 01:40:33,225
"Raye Anne, she's a stay in."

1402
01:40:33,293 --> 01:40:35,420
Anyway, a good friend of mine
used to say...

1403
01:40:35,496 --> 01:40:37,259
"This is a very simple game.

1404
01:40:37,331 --> 01:40:39,993
You throw the ball, you catch
the ball, you hit the ball.

1405
01:40:40,067 --> 01:40:43,264
Sometimes you win,
sometimes you lose.

1406
01:40:43,337 --> 01:40:46,363
Sometimes it rains."

1407
01:40:46,440 --> 01:40:48,032
Think about that for a while.

1408
01:42:20,734 --> 01:42:22,167
What happened?

1409
01:42:23,937 --> 01:42:25,029
l quit.

1410
01:42:27,808 --> 01:42:29,935
Hit my dinger
and l hung them up.

1411
01:42:36,950 --> 01:42:38,884
l'm quittin' too.

1412
01:42:38,952 --> 01:42:41,147
l mean boys,
not baseball.

1413
01:42:43,757 --> 01:42:47,887
There might be an opening for
a manager in Visalia next spring.

1414
01:42:52,399 --> 01:42:54,867
Think l could make it
to the Show as a manager?

1415
01:42:57,371 --> 01:42:59,339
You'd be great.

1416
01:43:04,611 --> 01:43:09,207
Because you understand about
nonlinear thinking.

1417
01:43:09,283 --> 01:43:13,310
Baseball seems like a linear game
with all those lines and box scores.

1418
01:43:13,387 --> 01:43:17,255
But the fact is, it's a spacious
non-time kind of time to it.

1419
01:43:18,392 --> 01:43:19,552
What?

1420
01:43:19,626 --> 01:43:23,357
l got a lot of time
to hear your theories.

1421
01:43:23,430 --> 01:43:26,194
And l wanna hear
every damn one of them, but...

1422
01:43:28,402 --> 01:43:31,701
now l'm tired and l don't want to
think about baseball.

1423
01:43:31,772 --> 01:43:34,468
And l don't wanna think
about quantum physics.

1424
01:43:34,541 --> 01:43:36,475
And l don't wanna
think about nothing.

1425
01:43:40,948 --> 01:43:43,416
l just wanna be.

1426
01:43:45,052 --> 01:43:46,986
l can do that too.

1427
01:43:49,423 --> 01:43:53,757
Walt Whitman once said,
"l see great things in baseball.

1428
01:43:53,827 --> 01:43:57,058
lt's our game.
The American game.

1429
01:43:57,130 --> 01:44:00,463
lt will repair our losses
and be a blessing to us."

1430
01:44:01,201 --> 01:44:03,192
You could look it up.
